<task id="AIPU2-115" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Verify audit log immutability</title>
    <phase>6</phase>
    <tags>testing, compliance, cosmos-db</tags>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-033</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    The audit log (AIPU2-033) must be immutable: no update or delete operations should be
    possible on audit entries after they are written. This is a compliance requirement for
    legal workspace AI usage — audit trails must be tamper-evident. This test verifies the
    immutability at the Cosmos DB level (RBAC / stored procedure restrictions) and at the
    API level (no update/delete endpoints exposed). Additionally, the retention policy must
    be verified to be set, and audit data must be exportable to Azure Blob for compliance
    archiving.
  </prompt>
  <role>Security engineer or compliance-focused developer.</role>
  <goal>
    Audit entries cannot be modified or deleted by any means available to the BFF API identity
    or through the audit API. Retention policy is confirmed set on the audit Cosmos container.
    Audit data can be exported to Azure Blob Storage. All findings documented in
    notes/audit-immutability-test-report.md.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r2/design.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Audit</file>
      <file>infrastructure/cosmos</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Write a test audit entry to the Cosmos audit container using the AuditLogService (AIPU2-033). Record the entry ID and etag.</step>
    <step>Attempt to update the audit entry directly via Cosmos SDK using the BFF Managed Identity (or a test identity with equivalent permissions). Assert the operation fails with a permission denied or precondition error.</step>
    <step>Attempt to delete the audit entry directly via Cosmos SDK. Assert deletion fails.</step>
    <step>Verify there are no BFF API endpoints that expose update or delete operations on audit records. Scan AuditEndpoints.cs and the audit service for any PATCH/PUT/DELETE handlers targeting audit records.</step>
    <step>Verify the Cosmos container TTL or retention policy: confirm the audit container has a TTL set to the required retention period (e.g. 7 years = 220752000 seconds) or that a separate Azure policy enforces retention.</step>
    <step>Test audit export to Azure Blob: trigger the export function (manual or via a test endpoint), verify that audit entries appear in the configured Azure Blob container as JSON or CSV, verify the export is complete and not truncated.</step>
    <step>Document all findings in notes/audit-immutability-test-report.md: test steps, expected vs. actual results, retention policy configuration, export verification.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Attempt to update an audit entry via Cosmos SDK fails with a permission or precondition error.</criterion>
    <criterion>Attempt to delete an audit entry via Cosmos SDK fails.</criterion>
    <criterion>No BFF API endpoint exposes update or delete operations on audit records.</criterion>
    <criterion>Cosmos audit container has a TTL or retention policy set to the required compliance period.</criterion>
    <criterion>Audit entries can be exported to Azure Blob Storage and the export is complete.</criterion>
    <criterion>Test report written to notes/audit-immutability-test-report.md with all findings.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
